The paper proposes a new architecture for solving working memory tasks using dual recurrent neural network controllers and a shared memory module. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, specifically in the sub-categories of deep learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multi-task learning, which is a common technique in computer science (cs.CC).
